            <abstract id="ref1" label="Abstract">Richard Nelson, long time member of the activist coalition Connecticut Stonewall Foundation, was an activist for gay, lesbian, bisexual and transgender rights. The collection includes materials pertaining to events put on by the Connecticut Stonewall Foundation and specific writing and speeches done by Richard Nelson.</abstract>
        </did>
        <bioghist id="ref2">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>The Connecticut Stonewall Foundation was founded in 1985. The group held educational seminars, lectures, events, and conferences to educate gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender people and the general public regarding GLBTQ contributions to the world’s culture, common history, and present day issues. Working with other organizations like The Gay, Lesbian, and Straight Teachers Network, Connecticut Women’s Education and Legal Fund, Children From the Shadows, CT NOW, The Women’s Center at Trinity College, The Gay &amp; Lesbian Film Festival, and various religious organizations, among others, the Foundation dealt with issues concerning the GLBTQ community culturally, politically, and socially. Richard Nelson was the Education Program Director of the Connecticut Stonewall Foundation and an avid activist for the gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender community in Connecticut.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref3">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The collection spans a time period from 1985 to 2008 and includes correspondence, newspaper articles, exhibit planning materials, memorabilia, brochures, and photographs.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <accessrestrict id="ref38">
